[[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 5 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 5 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[cdo:3 nguŏk 5 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 5 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 5 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-min-nan:5 goe̍h 5 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 5 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 5 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-yue:五月初五]] {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 5''' is the 5th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Gendoku|de|元徳|ja|元徳|zh|元徳|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year / {{ill|Genkō|de|元弘|ja|元弘|zh|元弘|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|Julian calendar|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1331|de|1331|ja|1331|zh|1331|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 10|de|June 10|ja|June 10|zh|June 10|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the rebellion known as {{ill|Genkō no Ran|de|元弘の乱|ja|元弘の乱|zh|元弘の乱|12=draft|12=draft}}, the reattempted anti-bakufu plot of Emperor {{ill|Go-Daigo|de|後醍醐天皇|ja|後醍醐天皇|zh|後醍醐天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} was leaked to the Ashikaga Shogunate, resulting in the arrest of figures such as {{ill|Hino Toshiki|de|日野俊基|ja|日野俊基|zh|日野俊基|12=draft|12=draft}}. The emperor then took refuge on 【Oki Province†Oki_Province】. * {{ill|Genna|de|Genna|ja|元和|zh|Genna|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1615|de|1615|ja|1615|zh|1615|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 1|de|June 1|ja|June 1|zh|June 1|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|de|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|zh|Tokugawa Ieyasu|12=draft|12=draft}} set out from Kyoto (from Nijō Castle) in preparation for the summer siege of Osaka. * {{ill|Tenmei|de|Tenmei|ja|天保|zh|Tenmei|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1786|de|1786|ja|1786|zh|1786|12=draft|12=draft}} June 1) – Under orders from the Tokugawa shogunate, the official {{ill|Mogami Tokunai|de|最上徳内|ja|最上徳内|zh|最上徳内|12=draft|12=draft}} landed on Ezo (specifically, on Etoroshima, also known as Etoroshima in Oki Province). == Births == * {{ill|Jōgan|de|Jōgan|ja|Jōgan|zh|Jōgan|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|Julian calendar|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|867|de|867|ja|867|zh|867|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 10|de|June 10|ja|June 10|zh|June 10|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Uta Tennō|de|宇多天皇|ja|宇多天皇|zh|宇多天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 59th Emperor of Japan (died [[931]]). * {{ill|Keichō|de|Keichō|ja|慶長|zh|Keichō|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1604|de|1604|ja|1604|zh|1604|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Uesugi Sadakatsu|de|上杉定勝|ja|上杉定勝|zh|上杉定勝|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 2nd lord of the Yonezawa Domain (died [[1645]]). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1642|de|1642|ja|1642|zh|1642|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yamaguchi Sodo|de|山口素堂|ja|山口素堂|zh|山口素堂|12=draft|12=draft}}, a haiku poet (died [[1716]]). * {{ill|Enkyō|ja|延享|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1746|de|1746|ja|1746|zh|1746|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 23|de|June 23|ja|June 23|zh|June 23|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hanawa Hokeiichi|de|塙保己一|ja|塙保己一|zh|塙保己一|12=draft|12=draft}}, a scholar of Japanese literature (died [[1821]]). * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|宝暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1763|de|1763|ja|1763|zh|1763|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 15|de|June 15|ja|June 15|zh|June 15|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kobayashi Issa|de|小林一茶|ja|小林一茶|zh|小林一茶|12=draft|12=draft}}, a haiku poet (died [[1827]]). * {{ill|Bunka|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1804|de|1804|ja|1804|zh|1804|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 12|de|June 12|ja|June 12|zh|June 12|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Takano Nagahide|de|高野長英|ja|高野長英|zh|高野長英|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Rangaku scholar (died [[1850]]). * {{ill|Bunka|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1828|de|1828|ja|1828|zh|1828|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 16|de|June 16|ja|June 16|zh|June 16|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hirose Sahei|de|広瀬宰平|ja|広瀬宰平|zh|広瀬宰平|12=draft|12=draft}}, a businessperson (died [[1914]]). * {{ill|Bunka|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1829|de|1829|ja|1829|zh|1829|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 6|de|June 6|ja|June 6|zh|June 6|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Honinbō Shūsaku|de|本因坊秀策|ja|本因坊秀策|zh|本因坊秀策|12=draft|12=draft}}, a professional Go player (died [[1862]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1835|de|1835|ja|1835|zh|1835|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|May 31|de|May 31|ja|May 31|zh|May 31|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hijikata Toshizō|de|土方歳三|ja|土方歳三|zh|土方歳三|12=draft|12=draft}}, vice-commander of the Shinsengumi (died [[1869]]). == Deaths == * {{ill|Enpō|ja|延宝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1680|de|1680|ja|1680|zh|1680|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 1|de|June 1|ja|June 1|zh|June 1|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hayashi Gahō|de|林鵞峰|ja|林鵞峰|zh|林鵞峰|12=draft|12=draft}} (Shunsai), a Zhu Xi scholar and son of Hayashi Rinsan (born {{ill|1618|de|1618|ja|1618|zh|1618|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Genji|ja|元治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|Gregorian calendar|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1864|de|1864|ja|1864|zh|1864|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 8|de|June 8|ja|June 8|zh|June 8|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Reisui Iguyasu|de|冷泉為恭|ja|冷泉為恭|zh|冷泉為恭|12=draft|12=draft}}, an imperial court painter. == Commemorations == * {{ill|Duanwu|de|Duanwu|ja|端午|zh|端午|12=draft|12=draft}} – The Dragon Boat Festival is celebrated. * Duanwu Festival (端午節) is observed in Taiwan. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jp.taiwantoday.tw/news.php?unit=151&post=115869|title=TAIWAN TODAY日本語版からのお知らせ|publisher=Taiwan Today|accessdate=2017-05-26}}</ref>
