(died [[:en:1645|1645]]). * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 19th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1642|1642]] {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 2|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Yamaguchi Sodo|de|山口素堂|ja|山口素堂|zh|山口素堂|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Sodo|qq=}}, a haiku poet (died [[:en:1716|1716]]). * [[:en:Enkyō (Edo period)|Enkyō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1746|1746]] {{ill|June 23|de|June 23|ja|June 23|zh|June 23|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 23|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Hanawa Hokiichi|Hanawa Hokeiichi]], a scholar of Japanese literature (died [[:en:1821|1821]]). * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 13rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1763|1763]] {{ill|June 15|de|June 15|ja|June 15|zh|June 15|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 15|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Kobayashi Issa|Kobayashi Issa]], a haiku poet (died [[:en:1827|1827]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunka]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1804|1804]] {{ill|June 12|de|June 12|ja|June 12|zh|June 12|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 12|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Takano Chōei|Takano Nagahide]], a Rangaku scholar (died [[:en:1850|1850]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunka]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1828|1828]] {{ill|June 16|de|June 16|ja|June 16|zh|June 16|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 16|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Saihei Hirose|Hirose Sahei]], a businessperson (died [[1914]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunka]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1829|1829]] {{ill|June 6|de|June 6|ja|June 6|zh|June 6|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 6|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Hon'inbō Shūsaku|Honinbō Shūsaku]], a professional Go player (died [[:en:1862|1862]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1835|1835]] {{ill|May 31|de|May 31|ja|May 31|zh|May 31|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 31|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Hijikata Toshizō|Hijikata Toshizō]], vice-commander of the Shinsengumi (died [[1869]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1680|1680]] {{ill|June 1|de|June 1|ja|June 1|zh|June 1|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 1|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Hayashi Gahō|Hayashi Gahō]] (Shunsai), a Zhu Xi scholar and son of Hayashi Rinsan (born [[:en:1618|1618]]). * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] {{ill|June 8|de|June 8|ja|June 8|zh|June 8|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 8|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – [[:en:Reizei Tamechika|Reisui Iguyasu]], an imperial court painter. == Commemorations == * [[:en:Dragon Boat Festival|Dragon Boat Festival]] – The Dragon Boat Festival is celebrated. * Duanwu Festival (端午節) is observed in Taiwan. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jp.taiwantoday.tw/news.php?unit=151&post=115869|title=TAIWAN TODAY日本語版からのお知らせ|publisher=Taiwan Today|accessdate=2017-05-26|qq=}}</ref>
