== Events == * {{ill|Gentoku|en|Gentoku|qid=Q1327385|lt=Gendoku|1=Gentoku}} 3rd year / {{ill|Genkō (1331–1334)|en|Genkō (1331–1334)|qid=Q1194556|lt=Genkō|1=Genkō (1331–1334)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1331|en|1331|qid=Q6000|lt=1331|1=1331}} {{ill|June 10|de|June 10|ja|June 10|zh|June 10|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 10|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – In the rebellion known as {{ill|Genkō War|en|Genkō War|qid=Q1432624|lt=Genkō no Ran|1=Genkō War}}, the reattempted anti-bakufu plot of Emperor {{ill|Emperor Go-Daigo|en|Emperor Go-Daigo|qid=Q313942|lt=Go-Daigo|1=Emperor Go-Daigo}} was leaked to the Ashikaga Shogunate, resulting in the arrest of figures such as {{ill|Hino Toshiki|de|日野俊基|ja|日野俊基|zh|日野俊基|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hino Toshiki|1=Hino Toshimoto|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11510567}}. The emperor then took refuge on 【Oki Province†Oki_Province】. * {{ill|Yuanhe|en|Yuanhe|qid=Q10889567|lt=Genna|1=Yuanhe}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1615|en|1615|qid=Q6784|lt=1615|1=1615}} {{ill|June 1|de|June 1|ja|June 1|zh|June 1|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 1|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|en|Tokugawa Ieyasu|qid=Q171977|lt=Tokugawa Ieyasu|1=Tokugawa Ieyasu}} set out from Kyoto (from Nijō Castle) in preparation for the summer siege of Osaka. * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenmei|1=Tenpō}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1786|en|1786|qid=Q7760|lt=1786|1=1786}} June 1) – Under orders from the Tokugawa shogunate, the official {{ill|Mogami Tokunai|en|Mogami Tokunai|qid=Q4141812|lt=Mogami Tokunai|1=Mogami Tokunai}} landed on Ezo (specifically, on Etoroshima, also known as Etoroshima in Oki Province). == Births == * {{ill|Jōgan|en|Jōgan|qid=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan|1=Jōgan}} 9th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|867|en|867|qid=Q30347|lt=867|1=867}} {{ill|June 10|de|June 10|ja|June 10|zh|June 10|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 10|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Emperor Uda|en|Emperor Uda|qid=Q349267|lt=Uta Tennō|1=Emperor Uda}}, the 59th Emperor of Japan (died {{ill|931|en|931|qid=Q24789|lt=931|1=931}}). * {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1604|en|1604|qid=Q6738|lt=1604|1=1604}} {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 2|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Uesugi Sadakatsu|de|上杉定勝|ja|上杉定勝|zh|上杉定勝|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uesugi Sadakatsu|1=Uesugi Sadakatsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q8514762}}, the 2nd lord of the Yonezawa Domain (died {{ill|1645|en|1645|qid=Q6925|lt=1645|1=1645}}). * {{ill|Kan'ei|en|Kan'ei|qid=Q1192913|lt=Kan'ei|1=Kan'ei}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1642|en|1642|qid=Q6912|lt=1642|1=1642}} {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 2|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Yamaguchi Sodo|de|山口素堂|ja|山口素堂|zh|山口素堂|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Sodo|1=Yamaguchi Sodō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11467412}}, a haiku poet (died {{ill|1716|en|1716|qid=Q6892|lt=1716|1=1716}}). * {{ill|Enkyō (Edo period)|en|Enkyō (Edo period)|qid=Q1183728|lt=Enkyō|1=Enkyō (Edo period)}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1746|en|1746|qid=Q7589|lt=1746|1=1746}} {{ill|June 23|de|June 23|ja|June 23|zh|June 23|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 23|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Hanawa Hokiichi|en|Hanawa Hokiichi|qid=Q6537362|lt=Hanawa Hokeiichi|1=Hanawa Hokiichi}}, a scholar of Japanese literature (died {{ill|1821|en|1821|qid=Q6976|lt=1821|1=1821}}). * {{ill|Hōreki|en|Hōreki|qid=Q1194397|lt=Hōreki|1=Hōreki}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1763|en|1763|qid=Q7655|lt=1763|1=1763}} {{ill|June 15|de|June 15|ja|June 15|zh|June 15|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 15|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Kobayashi Issa|en|Kobayashi Issa|qid=Q312709|lt=Kobayashi Issa|1=Kobayashi Issa}}, a haiku poet (died {{ill|1827|en|1827|qid=Q7008|lt=1827|1=1827}}). * {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunka|1=Bunsei}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1804|en|1804|qid=Q6894|lt=1804|1=1804}} {{ill|June 12|de|June 12|ja|June 12|zh|June 12|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 12|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Takano Chōei|en|Takano Chōei|qid=Q944693|lt=Takano Nagahide|1=Takano Chōei}}, a Rangaku scholar (died {{ill|1850|en|1850|qid=Q7653|lt=1850|1=1850}}). * {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunka|1=Bunsei}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1828|en|1828|qid=Q7570|lt=1828|1=1828}} {{ill|June 16|de|June 16|ja|June 16|zh|June 16|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 16|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Saihei Hirose|en|Saihei Hirose|qid=Q7400095|lt=Hirose Sahei|1=Saihei Hirose}}, a businessperson (died {{ill|1914|en|1914|qid=Q2083|lt=1914|1=1914}}). * {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunka|1=Bunsei}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1829|en|1829|qid=Q7572|lt=1829|1=1829}} {{ill|June 6|de|June 6|ja|June 6|zh|June 6|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 6|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Hon'inbō Shūsaku|en|Hon'inbō Shūsaku|qid=Q511141|lt=Honinbō Shūsaku|1=Hon'inbō Shūsaku}}, a professional Go player (died {{ill|1862|en|1862|qid=Q7698|lt=1862|1=1862}}). * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1835|en|1835|qid=Q7597|lt=1835|1=1835}} {{ill|May 31|de|May 31|ja|May 31|zh|May 31|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 31|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Hijikata Toshizō|en|Hijikata Toshizō|qid=Q701182|lt=Hijikata Toshizō|1=Hijikata Toshizō}}, vice-commander of the Shinsengumi (died {{ill|1869|en|1869|qid=Q7720|lt=1869|1=1869}}). == Deaths == * {{ill|Enpō|en|Enpō|qid=Q1145735|lt=Enpō|1=Enpō}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1680|en|1680|qid=Q7642|lt=1680|1=1680}} {{ill|June 1|de|June 1|ja|June 1|zh|June 1|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 1|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Hayashi Gahō|en|Hayashi Gahō|qid=Q3128811|lt=Hayashi Gahō|1=Hayashi Gahō}} (Shunsai), a Zhu Xi scholar and son of Hayashi Rinsan (born {{ill|1618|en|1618|qid=Q6801|lt=1618|1=1618}}). * {{ill|Genji era|en|Genji era|qid=Q1325419|lt=Genji|1=Genji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1864|en|1864|qid=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}} {{ill|June 8|de|June 8|ja|June 8|zh|June 8|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 8|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Reizei Tamechika|en|Reizei Tamechika|qid=Q11395355|lt=Reisui Iguyasu|1=Reizei Tamechika}}, an imperial court painter. == Commemorations == * {{ill|Dragon Boat Festival|en|Dragon Boat Festival|qid=Q1254268|lt=Dragon Boat Festival|1=Dragon Boat Festival}} – The Dragon Boat Festival is celebrated. * Duanwu Festival (端午節) is observed in Taiwan. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jp.taiwantoday.tw/news.php?unit=151&post=115869|title=TAIWAN TODAY日本語版からのお知らせ|publisher=Taiwan Today|accessdate=2017-0